      "Apache Corporation retraining Crane Operator"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 2, 2023, at 12:30 hours, during crane operations at High Island A 382 F facility, the crane boom contacted the boom stop when raised to too high an angle, causing damage to the boom heel section cords. The Crane Operator was focusing on booming up and holding the ball level when the load block swung into the crane boom. The High Angle Kick Out limit switch failed to stop the boom from booming up too far. The incident resulted in $50,000 in estimated replacement costs with no injuries or pollution. The investigation concluded that Crane Operator inattentiveness of the boom angle was the primary cause, with the failure of the high angle kick out safety system as a contributing factor.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Apache Corporation is Retraining Crane Operator"
    ],
